'''伊拉克戰爭調查'''（{{lang-en|'''Iraq Inquiry'''}}），因其主席{{le|約翰·齊爾考特|John Chilcot}}亦稱為「'''齊爾考特調查'''」（{{lang|en|'''Chilcot Inquiry'''}}）<ref name=Guardian1>[http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/2009/jul/31/iraq-inquiry-fourth-plinth-chilcot My alternative to another round of Iraq whitewashing] {{Wayback|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/2009/jul/31/iraq-inquiry-fourth-plinth-chilcot |date=20111205161358 }} ''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]'', 2009-07-31.</ref><ref name=Guardian2>[http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/2009/aug/14/british-army-abuses-iraq-chilcot-inquiry Investigate UK abuses in Iraq] {{Wayback|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/2009/aug/14/british-army-abuses-iraq-chilcot-inquiry |date=20120910120252 }} ''The Guardian'', 2009-08-14.</ref>，是一個目的為調查英國在[[伊拉克戰爭|伊拉克戰爭]]扮演之角色的英國{{le|政府調查|public inquiry}}。該調查於2007年由時任[[英國首相|首相]][[白高敦|白高敦]]宣佈展開，在2016年由齊爾考特發表公開聲明及報告。

該調查是由一群[[英國樞密院|英國樞密院]]成員組成的調查委員會進行。委員會被委託調查的範圍廣闊，以檢視英國於2001至2009年間介入伊拉克的行動。調查範圍包括{{le|伊拉克戰爭的前奏|Lead-up to the Iraq War}}、[[伊拉克戰爭|英國的軍事行動]]及[[伊拉克內戰|戰爭的後果]]，以確立當時作出決定的過程、確定當時發生了什麼以及找出當中任何經驗或教訓，以確保英國政府在往後遇到相似的情況時，能以最有效及以最合符國家利益下作出回應<ref name=BBC6>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk_politics/7312757.stm |title=The key points of the Iraq war inquiry explained |publisher=BBC News |date=2010-03-05 |accessdate=2016-07-31 |archive-date=2016-07-06 |archive-url=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20160706221205/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk_politics/7312757.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。調查的公聽部分於2009年11月24日開始，於2011年2月2日完結。

2012年，英國政府否決向調查委員會提供在{{le|2003年進攻伊拉克|2003 invasion of Iraq}}前數天的內閣會議會議紀錄。同時，[[英國外交及聯邦事務部|外交及聯邦事務部]]上訴成功，推翻了先前一名法官的判決，成功阻止向調查透露在進攻前數天[[貝理雅|貝理雅]]和[[喬治·獲嘉·布殊|喬治·獲嘉·布殊]]對話的內容。政府指，如果透露這些對話的內容會「嚴重危害」[[英美關係|英美關係]]<ref name="dailymail.co.uk">John Kampfner, ''[[Daily_Mail|Daily Mail]]'', 2012-08-03, [http://www.dailymail.co.uk/debate/article-2182924/Chilcot-inquiry-Hypocrisy-insidious-culture-secrecy.html Hypocrisy and this insidious culture of secrecy] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/debate/article-2182924/Chilcot-inquiry-Hypocrisy-insidious-culture-secrecy.html |date=20120805233359 }}</ref>。調查報告原訂於2014年向公眾公開<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/iraq/10191047/Foreign-Office-braced-for-criticism-in-Chilcot-report-over-its-record-keeping-around-Iraq-War.html|title=Foreign Office braced for criticism in Chilcot report over its record-keeping around Iraq War|date=2013-01-20|work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]]|publisher=[[Telegraph_Media_Group|Telegraph Media Group]]|accessdate=2013-01-20|location=London|first=Christopher|last=Hope|archive-date=2019-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609155121/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/iraq/10191047/Foreign-Office-braced-for-criticism-in-Chilcot-report-over-its-record-keeping-around-Iraq-War.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但是由於[[美國國務院|美國國務院]]不同意公佈報告，英美雙方所以需要進行談判<ref>James Cusick, ''[[The_Independent|The Independent]]'', 2011-11-13, [http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/exclusive-us-blocks-publication-of-chilcots-report-on-how-britain-went-to-war-with-iraq-8937772.html Exclusive: US blocks publication of Chilcot's report on how Britain went to war with Iraq ] {{Wayback|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/exclusive-us-blocks-publication-of-chilcots-report-on-how-britain-went-to-war-with-iraq-8937772.html |date=20150925170225 }}</ref>。

2015年5月，{{le|索爾泰爾華萊士男爵威廉·華萊士|William Wallace, Baron Wallace of Saltaire|索爾泰爾華萊士男爵}}代表政府指出，於下一屆英國大選前數個月發表報告「不適宜」<ref name=BBCNov314>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-29884094|title=Iraq Inquiry set to cost taxpayers £10m|publisher=[[BBC_News_Online|BBC News Online]]|date=2014-11-03|accessdate=2014-11-14|archive-date=2014-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141112212543/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-29884094|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2015年8月，由於英國法律訂明在報告最終完成前，報告中被批評者必需有機會對草案發表意見，所以報告的發佈日期再次被押後至2016年<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/iraq-war-chilcot-inquiry-sir-john-chilcot-a6969046.html|title=Iraq War: MPs launch investigation into legislation which delayed Chilcot Inquiry|author=Matt Broomfield|date=2016-04-05|accessdate=2016-01-20|newspaper=Independent|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108100259/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/iraq-war-chilcot-inquiry-sir-john-chilcot-a6969046.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2015年10月，約翰·齊爾考特致函時任英揆[[大衛·金馬倫|大衛·金馬倫]]，宣佈報告將於2016年4月完成，並建議於2016年7月公開<ref>{{cite web|title=Chilcot report: David Cameron's full reply to summer 2016 publication of Iraq War inquiry|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/chilcot-report-david-camerons-full-reply-summer-2016-publication-iraq-war-inquiry-1526291|website=International Business Times|date=2015-10-29|accessdate=2016-07-31|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108123927/https://www.ibtimes.co.uk/chilcot-report-david-camerons-full-reply-summer-2016-publication-iraq-war-inquiry-1526291|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2016年7月6日，調查委員會主席約翰·齊爾考特發佈調查報告，距宣佈開始調查超過七年<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Iraq Inquiry: Chilcot report to be published on 6 July |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36251346 |publisher=BBC News |date=2016-05-09 |access-date=2016-05-09 |archive-date=2016-05-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160510000610/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36251346 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，報告常被英文媒體稱為「'''齊爾考特報告'''」（'''Chilcot report'''）<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-36721645 |title=Chilcot report: Findings at-a-glance |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2016-07-07 |website=BBC |publisher=BBC |access-date=2016-07-07 |archive-date=2016-07-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160707052705/http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-36721645 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。報告內容則指出當時[[薩達姆·侯賽因|薩達姆·侯賽因]]對英國利益並無造成迫切的威脅、英國情報部門當時並不確定伊拉克擁有[[大規模殺傷性武器|大規模殺傷性武器]]、英國政府當時仍未用盡戰爭以外和平解決的方法、英美兩國削弱了[[聯合國安全理事會|聯合國安全理事會]]的權威、當時尋找法律依據進攻伊拉克的過程「強差人意」，以及於2003年並無必要發動戰爭<ref name="GuardianReport">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/jul/06/chilcot-report-crushing-verdict-tony-blair-iraq-war|title=Chilcot delivers crushing verdict on Blair and the Iraq war|author=Luke Harding|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2016-07-06|accessdate=2016-07-06|archive-date=2016-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160707153638/https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/jul/06/chilcot-report-crushing-verdict-tony-blair-iraq-war|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="TelegraphReport">{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/07/06/chilcot-inquiry-judgement-day-for-tony-blair-as-iraq-war-report/|title=Chilcot report: 2003 Iraq war was 'unnecessary', invasion was not 'last resort' and Saddam Hussein was 'no imminent threat'|author=Leon Watson|date=2016-07-06|accessdate=2016-07-06|newspaper=The Telegraph|archive-date=2016-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160706073911/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/07/06/chilcot-inquiry-judgement-day-for-tony-blair-as-iraq-war-report/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。該報告以{{le|Open Government Licence|Open Government Licence}}下授權發佈。

